\subsection{Recuperation and Upkeep}
\label{recuperation}

\subsubsection{The rate at which Endurance Points are recovered depends
on how active the injured being is.}
d265 1
a265 4
If a being expends and/or loses no more than one-half his Fatigue
Points (round down) for three consecutive days, he regains one
Endurance Point at the end of the third day.  Otherwise, he recovers
an Endurance Point at the end of the following (i.e., fourth) day.
d267 2
a268 2
If a being is given ministrations from a physicker's kit, his body
requires one less day to regain an Endurance Point.
d270 2
a271 3
\subsubsection{Injuries which are not quantified as Endurance Point
losses (e.g., hamstrung muscles) heal at the same rate as they do in
this world.}
d273 64
a336 4
The GM should assume that an Endurance value of 15 indicates a body
which heals in average time.  Values greater than 15 will allow a
being to heal more quickly, while values lower than 15 will cause a
corresponding extension to the time required.
